rComments: Professor Rouhi is very passionate about teaching. He really tries to make sure that the class understands the points he is trying to make, and likes to make the class interactive. The course requires that you really understand the material, and the exams reflect this. I needed to work more out of class than I expected. The class was hard, but fair

One of the best teachers I have had. Really cares about you understanding the concepts. However, not clear on deliverables such as HWs, quizzes etc but made up for it by being very lenient in grading.
Gives clear and easy to comprehend lectures, very much enjoyed this class
He is an amazing professor. The course itself is hard and heavy but he did his best to teach us. Prepare yourself for a tough course!
I found the professor very caring and patient. He offers tasks to students who may not be satisfied with their own performance and want to do better in the course.

Great lecturer and fair grader. You have sit in the front row if you want to hear anything because he talks way too quietly. He trys his best to help u at his office hours. Only problem is that the course he teaches is pure math and requires an extensive grasp of the contents.
He is very good professor. Teaching and grade is fair. Good professor. Please choose his course.

Really great, down to earth guy, always gives traditional iranain sweets in his office. Exams and grading is fair. Only problems are that his answers to questions are really vague which in the end isn't really helpful, he talks TOO QUIETLY so you need extra attentiveness to pick up stuff, also the lights are always off, so good luck not sleeping.
